  "_meta": {
    "purpose": "SEARCH-04 behavioral golden-query ranking net. Pins the ordered top-N result identity for a representative set of queries so a ranking refactor (e.g. SEARCH-02 de-bloat) can be proven behavior-preserving. Unlike the recall-threshold keyword-regression harness, this asserts EXACT ordering.",
    "scope": "Captured against the LOCAL wrangler-dev corpus (~14k docs). env.AI is inert locally, so the vector stage is skipped and this pins the lexical + decision-layer ranking — which is exactly the surface SEARCH-02 refactors. The production vector contribution is out of scope for this net.",
    "endpoint": "POST /admin/retrieval/debug",
    "idField": "citation, falling back to documentId",
    "regenerate": "Start the local server, then: UPDATE_SEARCH_GOLDEN=1 pnpm --filter @beedle/api test:search-golden  (review the diff before committing — only regenerate when the corpus or an intended ranking change explains it).",
